title: full-body_blush

title: ayrton_senna
body:
[b]Ayrton Senna da Silva[/b] (b. March 21, 1960, d. May 1st, 1994).

A famous Brazilian [[formula one|Formula 1]] driver and three-time World Champion who raced in F1 from 1984 to 1994. Died in a crash during the 1994 San Marino Grand Prix. Widely considered one the greatest drivers in the sport.

title: fujibayashi_suzu
body: A supporting protagonist from [[Tales of Phantasia]] who is a trained ninja despite being 11 years old. She masks her emotions due to the ninja way of suppressing one's feelings, but has a sweet tooth. She shares the same last name as [[Fujibayashi Sheena]], but no official relationship between them is stated. Suzu is the youngest playable character in the entire [[tales of (series)|Tales of...]] franchise. Her seiyuu is [[Kawata Taeko]].

title: kazagumo_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Kazagumo[/i]. Character designed by [[Nagu]], voiced by [[Itou Ayasa]]. 

She is portrayed with [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] tied into [[twin braids]], and [[animal ears|avian ears]]. Her default outfit is a [[serafuku]] theme and consists of a [[black shirt]] with a [[white sailor collar]], [[orange neckerchief]], [[white skirt|white]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[high-waist skirt]], [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[black jacket]], [[black hat|black]] [[beret]], [[mismatched legwear|differently-colored socks]] ([[orange socks|orange left]] and [[black socks|black right]]), and [[black shoes|black]] [[Mary Janes]]. 

Her [[rigging]] consists of a hull piece to her back containing a quad 61 cm [[torpedo tubes]] and a 12.7 cm twin gun mount, with a second gun mount with wings.

title: combat_medic
body:
[b]Combat medics[/b], or simply [b]medics[/b], are [[military]] personnel who have received at least basic level Emergency Medical Technician (EMT) training and are responsible for providing first aid and frontline trauma care on the battlefield. They typically wear [[red cross]] attributes to indicate that they are combat medics.

title: meisho_doto_(dot-o'-lantern)_(umamusume)
body:
[[Halloween]]-themed skin for [[Meisho Doto (umamusume)|]] from [[Umamusume]], introduced in the [i]Days in a Flash[/i] event.

It consists of an [[orange hat|orange]] [[pumpkin hat]], a [[short_dress|short]] [[black_dress|black]] [[layered dress]] with [[juliet sleeves]], a [[white ascot]] with an [[orange_ribbon|orange]] [[neck ribbon]] and a [[jack-o'-lantern ornament]], an [[underbust]] [[black corset]] with a [[large_bow|large]] orange [[back bow]], a [[torn pantyhose|torn]] [[black pantyhose]] and [[blue_shoes|blue]] [[high heels]]. Her hairband is now [[purple_hairband|purple]] and wears a [[single ear cover]] instead of a ribbon.

This skin is infamous for it's G1 victory animation, where Doto is pointing to something up and away from the viewer, somewhere off-screen (likely the scoreboard). When used in a legend race or something that displays a losing character above her, it looks like she's pointing to mock them.

title: chien_wu_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s representation of Chinese cruiser Chien Wu.

Her historical counterpart is the cruiser No.68. Designed by Monfalcone of Austria Hungary, it was laid down but never completed during World War I.

She is voiced by [[Mizuno Saku]].

title: pixel-perfect_duplicate
body:
A post that is completely identical to its parent down to the pixel and was either uploaded afterwards or has no source while their parent does, and thus is inferior for Danbooru purposes.

If a PNG with a vastly larger filesize to a JPG is a pixel-perfect duplicate, [[lossy-lossless]] may also apply.

Pixiv and Twitter posts are often identical, even if they have different filesizes. In 2019 Twitter stopped compressing as harshly as they used to and in late 2020 Pixiv started losslessly recompressing their JPGs to strip metadata, so typically if there's only a few KBs of difference between two identical pictures from these two sites, it means they're the exact same image.

There are three ways to know if similar images are pixel-perfect duplicates:

* In the uploader, a red label at the bottom will show if the image is identical to another. Check the similar tab to find the existing post.
* From the image's asset page, click on Pixel Hash to reveal posts and assets that have the same Pixel Hash. These are pixel-perfect duplicates.
** An image's asset page can be opened by clicking on the text below the image in the uploader showing the filesize, file type and resolution or by clicking the two arrows beside the resolution on a post's page.
* Use https://duplicatebooru.zipfiled.info.

For posts already uploaded, the post with the lowest id should be the parent, and the rest should be tagged as pixel-perfect duplicate and parented to it.

[s]This tag is automatically populated and should not be removed by users.[/s] Uploaders should avoid posting duplicates. For duplicates already posted, uploaders are responsible for properly tagging and parenting their duplicates to the existing post.

[b]Do not flag posts just because they are under this tag if they come from a first-party source.[/b]

title: emperor's_new_clothes
body:
An [[Andersen's Fairy Tales|Andersen fairy tale]] about a vain and hedonistic emperor who gets fooled into walking around town while "wearing" supposedly invisible clothes that only smart people can see, and his people being reluctant to believe and/or admit the truth until an innocent child points out that the emperor is actually [[completely nude]]. Known in Japan as "Naked Emperor".

The name is sometimes used idiomatically to describe the phenomenon of "pluralistic ignorance":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pluralistic_ignorance].

Apply this tag when the character alludes their state of nudity to the folklore (such as referring their cloth as the one that only X could see, etc.), or depicts the scene of the original tale.

title: egor_letov
body:
[b]Egor Letov[/b] (Born Igor Fyodorovich Letov, September 10, 1964 – February 19, 2008) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] and [[Russia|Russian]] musician, poet, and conceptual artist, often called the "godfather of Russian punk." He founded the influential post-punk band [[Grazhdanskaya Oborona]] (Civil Defense) in 1984 and led other projects like [b]Egor i Opizdenevshie[/b] and the avant-garde collective [b]Kommunizm[/b]. 

His raw, rebellious music and surreal themes explored chaos, freedom, and alienation, often clashing with Soviet authorities—leading to his 1985 internment in a mental hospital by the [[KGB]].

Letov collaborated with Siberian underground artists like [[Yanka Dyagileva|]] and produced experimental works regarding blending punk, psychedelia, and absurdism.

title: grazhdanskaya_oborona
body:
[b]Grazhdanskaya Oborona[/b] (Meaning "Civil Defense") was a pioneering [[Soviet_union|Soviet]] and [[Russia|Russian]] post-punk band formed in 1984 in Omsk by [[Egor Letov]], its lead singer and songwriter. 

A cornerstone of Russian [[punk]], the band was known for its raw sound and provocative, anti-establishment lyrics that challenged Soviet authority, often facing censorship and harassment. Their music evolved from gritty punk to include psychedelic and experimental elements, with iconic albums like [b]Myshelovka[/b] (1987) and [b]Russkoe Pole Eksperimentov[/b] (1989).

A female character first introduced in [[Devil May Cry 3]]. Real name Mary Ann Arkham.
She renounces her name after her mother's death at the hands of her father [[Arkham (devil_may_cry)|]], becoming a demon hunter.

[[Dante (devil_may_cry)|]] nicknames her Lady as she refuses to give him a name to call her by, she then later takes this nickname as her new name.
Seeing Dante shed tears over the loss of his brother she coins the phrase "devil may cry" which inspired him to use as the name of his business.

She is fully human and has no demonic power and so fights mainly with guns and explosives. Her signature weapon is a [[kalina ann (weapon)|rocket launcher]] bearing the name of her deceased mother.

title: yang_xiao_long
body:
One of the main characters of [[RWBY]]. Yang is the "Y" in RWBY, and is associated with the color yellow. Her character design is inspired by [[Goldilocks]].

She has [[purple eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[wavy hair|wavy]] [[blonde hair]] with an [[ahoge]], and has fairly [[large breasts]]. 

She wields a pair of [[shotgun]]/gauntlet (technically [[vambraces]]) hybrid weapons named [[ember_celica_(rwby)|Ember Celica]], classified as "Dual Ranged Shot Gauntlets" (DRSG). Her weapons eject [[shell_casing|shell casings]]. Her symbol is a burning heart. Her eyes turn [[red eyes|red]] and [[fire]] surrounds her when her semblance (special ability) activates, which converts the damage she takes into additional strength. 

Yang tends to wear yellow/orange/brown/black clothing. Her default outfit includes a long [[orange scarf]] wrapped around her neck, a [[midriff]]-baring [[brown jacket]] with [[puffy short sleeves]] over a [[cleavage]]-revealing [[yellow shirt|yellow]] [[tube top]], [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]] underneath her weapon Ember Celica, a brown [[belt]] with [[buckle]] that secures a short [[waist cape]] over [[black shorts|black]] [[shorts]], an [[uneven legwear|asymmetrical]] pair of [[kneehighs|kneehigh]] and [[over-kneehighs|over-kneehigh]] socks, and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[high heel boots|high heel]] [[knee boots]]. 

Her Beacon [[school uniform]] consists of a [[white shirt|white]] [[blouse]] with [[neck ribbon]], brown [[blazer]], and [[plaid skirt]]. 

[[Ruby Rose]] is her half-sister. She loves her family, her hair, her [[motorcycle]], and fights. Guilty of bad puns. 

[spoiler]At the end of Season 3 of RWBY, Yang has her right arm severed at the elbow by [[Adam Taurus]], and in Season 4 receives a [[prosthetic_arm|prosthetic replacement]].[/spoiler]

body:

title: traitor_magolor
body:
Traitor Magolor is the form [[Magolor]] takes in [i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land]][/i] and [i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land Deluxe]][/i], after he puts on the [[Master Crown]]. This form is larger and more menacing, with differences such as an aura-like body, a larger crown with claws on his head, curved horns, and larger hands connected to star-shaped glyphs. He can float higher than the original Magolor, and has new magic attacks.

In Extra Mode, this form is known as Traitor Magolor EX, and has a black and red [[official alternate color]].

During battle, this form is simply referred to as Magolor or Magolor EX. The names Traitor Magolor and Traitor Magolor EX come from [i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land Deluxe]][/i], where masks of his face are given unique names.

Once he is defeated, he enters a second phase. In Story Mode [[Magolor (2nd form)|this form]] is unnamed, but the Extra Mode counterpart is uniquely named [[Magolor Soul]].

body: Gavel is a small ceremonial [[mallet]] used to strike a sound block, to call attention or punctuate rulings in a court of law.

title: rush_(mega_man)
body:
A multipurpose [[robot dog]] created by [[Dr. Light (mega man)|]] to help [[Mega Man (character)|]], first introduced in [[Mega Man 3]].

It has a [[spring (object)|]] to help Mega Man jump to hard-to-reach platforms, it can transform into a submarine to facilitate movement underwater and transform into a jet for quick stage traversal, among many other abilities.

It can also fuse with Mega Man, turning him into [[Super Mega Man (mega man)|]].

title: k2_black_panther
body:
The [b]K2 Black Panther[/b] is a [[South Korea]]n [[tank|main battle]] [[tank]] manufactured by "Hyundai Rotem":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyundai_Rotem. 

The design began in 1995 to meet the strategic requirements of the [[Republic of Korea Army]]'s reform for three-dimensional, high-speed maneuver warfare based on use of network-centric [[war]]fare.

Mass production commenced in 2013, and the first K2s were deployed with the South Korean [[military|armed forces]] in July 2014.

title: kamen_rider_knight_survive
body:
[[Kamen Rider Knight]]'s power up form.

h4. List of [[Advent Card|Advent Cards]] owned
* [b]Sword Vent[/b]: Split [[Dark Visor Zwei]] into two parts: the [[sword]] named ‘[b]Dark Blade[/b]’ and the [[shield]] named ‘[b]Dark Shield[/b]’. It is possible to split without using this card.
* [b]Shoot Vent[/b]: Transforms the Dark Visor Zwei into its [[crossbow]] form, the ‘[b]Dark Arrow[/b]’. It is capable of shooting [[energy arrow]] by absorbing sunlight.
* [b]Blust Vent[/b]: [[DarkRaider]] spins its wing wheels to create a gust of wind called a ‘[b]Dark Storm[/b]’, which blows the target away.
** In “[[Kamen Rider Dragon Knight]]”, the name was changed to “[b]Blast Vent[/b]”.
* [b]Trick Vent[/b]: He activates ‘[b]Shadow Illusion[/b]’, the special move that creates multiple [[clone|clones]] of himself.
* [b]Final Vent[/b]: Launch ‘[b]Shippuu-Dan[/b]’, the most powerful special move. Drives DarkRaider that has been transformed into motorbike form and wraps itself in [[cloak|cloaks]] around the entire vehicle body before transforming into a missile form and charging forward. It can also fire a special beam before charging, disabling the target.

title: hercules_beetle
body:
A species of [[rhinoceros beetle]], and the longest species of beetle in the world. Male hercules beetles have a gigantic horn on their prothorax, as well as immense strength for their size.

Males have black bodies, outside their elytra (wing cases), which are shades of olive-green with black spots and are divided by a black suture. Females lack the species' characteristic horns, and are mostly black outside a quarter of the elytra, which may have the same color pattern as males.

Street snaps are commonly featured in fashion magazines around the world, as they help showcase what kind of clothing is currently being worn by everyday people.

title: mikan_box
body:
A [[box]] used to pack mikan ([[mandarin orange|mandarin oranges]]). They can be distinguished by "みかん" or an orange being printed on the box. The mikan box is a recurring trope in anime and manga, with a disproportionate fraction of all cardboard boxes being mikan boxes. In particular, a kitten or puppy abandoned by the side of the road is almost always in a mikan box.

h4. External links

* "StackExchange: Why is the mikan so popular in anime and manga?":[https://anime.stackexchange.com/questions/7252/why-is-the-mikan-so-popular-in-anime-and-manga]

title: harpoon_missile
body:
First introduced in 1977, the Harpoon missile uses active radar homing, and a low-level, sea-skimming cruise trajectory to improve survivability and lethality. It is available in the following versions as listed:

AGM-84: for use on aircraft
RGM-84: for use on naval vessels and coastal batteries; this version has an solid rocket booster that detaches when it is empty
UGM-84: Same as the RGM model but the SRB is encased in a container to allow for use via a submarine's torpedo tubes. This version was retired in 1997.

title: harpoon_gun
body:
A weapon/fishing tool and a variant of [[harpoon]]. As its name implies, it (typically) fires harpoon at a target to either drive it away or to restrain it with a tied rope on  the other end of the harpoon to prevent them from escaping.

While there exists a harpoon gun that doesn't fire an actual harpoon (as some fire an explosive projectile instead, similar to an actual [[cannon]]). For tagging purposes, this tag is specifically refers to the "traditional" harpoon gun that fires harpoon, as such, apply this tag when the harpoon is visible on the device.

title: eventier_(masterwork_apocalypse)
body:
Character from [[Masterwork Apocalypse]].

[b]Origin:[/b] [[Andersen's Fairy Tales]], consisting of 156 stories across nine volumes and translated into more than 125 languages, Hans Christian Andersen's Fairy Tales have become culturally embedded in the West's collective consciousness, readily accessible to children, but presenting lessons of virtue and resilience in the face of adversity for mature readers as well. His most famous fairy tales include "The Emperor's New Clothes," "The Little Mermaid," "The Nightingale," "The Steadfast Tin Soldier", "The Red Shoes", "The Princess and the Pea," "The Snow Queen," "The Ugly Duckling," "The Little Match Girl," and "Thumbelina"
[b]Japanese voice actress:[/b] [[Horie Yui]]

title: energy_barrier
body:
A barrier created out of any sort of energy, including [[magic|magical]] and [[psychic]] energy.  Frequently the energy produces a [[transparent]] wall, screen, or bubble, but may also be used for creating things such as surfaces for walking on.  Energy barriers are a common feature in [[science fiction]] and [[fantasy]].

Energy barriers are most frequently used to defend against attacks, but may also serve as screens restricting passage, prisons for entrapping a target, or even an attack by pushing the field of energy outward into nearby targets.

title: simirror
body:
A type of character that appears in the [[Kirby (series)|Kirby series]]. He first appeared in [[Kirby Super Star]].
He looks like a [[magician]] and uses his [[mage staff]] to create a [[mirror]]-like [[energy_barrier|barrier]] that reflects [[Kirby]]'s attacks.
Swallowing him would copy the [[Mirror kirby|Mirror]] ability.

title: kine_(kirby)
body:
An ocean sunfish who befriends [[kirby|Kirby]] in [i][[kirby's_dream_land_2|Kirby's Dream Land 2]][/i] and [i][[kirby's_dream_land_3|Kirby's Dream Land 3]][/i]. He allows Kirby to swim more efficiently and synergizes with [[copy_ability|copy abilities]] in ways that can behave differently based on land and water.

After a number of cameos since then, he makes a return in [i][[kirby star allies|Kirby Star Allies]][/i] alongside fellow animal friends [[rick_(kirby)|Rick]] and [[coo_(kirby)|Coo]], where the trio comes together as a Dream Friend. They were part of the first wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[marx (kirby)|Marx]] and [[gooey (kirby)|Gooey]].

title: rick_(kirby)
body:
A friendly and energetic [[hamster]] who befriends [[kirby|Kirby]] in [i][[kirby's_dream_land_2|Kirby's Dream Land 2]][/i] and [i][[kirby's_dream_land_3|Kirby's Dream Land 3]][/i]. Besides being able to synergize with Kirby's [[copy_ability|copy abilities]], he can jump on enemies and climb up walls.

After a number of cameos since then, he makes a return in [i][[kirby star allies|Kirby Star Allies]][/i] alongside fellow animal friends [[kine_(kirby)|Kine]] and [[coo_(kirby)|Coo]], where the trio comes together as a Dream Friend. They were part of the first wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[marx (kirby)|Marx]] and [[gooey (kirby)|Gooey]].

title: coo_(kirby)
body:
A purple [[owl]] that befriends [[kirby|Kirby]] in [i][[kirby's_dream_land_2|Kirby's Dream Land 2]][/i] and [i][[kirby's_dream_land_3|Kirby's Dream Land 3]][/i]. Besides being able to synergize with Kirby's [[copy_ability|copy abilities]], he gives Kirby better flight control and speed.

After a number of cameos since then, he makes a return in [i][[kirby star allies|Kirby Star Allies]][/i] alongside fellow animal friends [[rick_(kirby)|Rick]] and [[kine_(kirby)|Kine]], where the trio comes together as a Dream Friend. They were part of the first wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[marx (kirby)|Marx]] and [[gooey (kirby)|Gooey]].

Do not confuse with [[fishnets]].

title: hand_net
body:
A simple device used for capturing composed of a mesh netting bag framed around the opening with a handle attached.  The shape and size of the frame, handle length, and type of netting used varies depending on what the device was built to catch.

The most common type depicted here are [[butterfly net]]s, but other types of hand nets include, but are not limited to, those use for catching fish, animals, or even skimming leaves from a pool.

title: laser_kirby
body:
An occasional [[copy ability]] throughout the [[kirby (series)|Kirby]] series that lets [[Kirby]] fire a [[laser]] at enemies.

In this form, Kirby only gains the use of a red and white [[umbrella]] with a [[star ornament|star]] on the tip.

In this form, Kirby wears many [[leaf on head|leaves on his head]] like a [[crown]] with a [[green gemstone]] in its center.

body:
A [[copy ability]] that appears in [[Kirby: Triple Deluxe]] and the [[Kirby Fighters 2|Kirby Fighters series]] which lets [[Kirby]] use [[bell|bells]] as weapons.

When in this form, Kirby wears a large [[gold headwear|gold]] [[hat bell|bell as a hat]] with a [[star hat ornament|star]] in its center, as well as a [[blue ribbon|blue]] [[hat ribbon]] around the bell's ring.

title: circus_kirby
body:
A [[copy ability]] that appears in [[Kirby: Triple Deluxe]] and [[Kirby: Planet Robobot]] which lets [[Kirby]] use several [[circus|circus-themed]] [[attack|attacks]].

When in this form, Kirby wears a [[striped headwear|striped]] [[hat]] that resembles a circus tent with a notable [[clown nose]] and [[fake mustache]] on it.

title: doctor_kirby

A [[copy ability]] that appears in [[Kirby: Planet Robobot]], [[Team Kirby Clash Deluxe]], and [[Super Kirby Clash]] which turns [[Kirby]] into a [[doctor]], letting him create one of four unique [[potion|potions]].

When in this form, Kirby wears a [[white coat|white]] [[lab coat]] with notable [[coattails]], a [[head mirror]] on a [[blue headband]], and [[round eyewear|round]] [[blue-framed eyewear|blue-framed]] [[glasses]].

title: hummingbird
body:
Latin: [i]Trochilidae[/i] family
JP: ハチドリ [i]hachidori[/i]

The smallest [[bird]]s in the world, renowned for their ability to hover in place and even fly backwards. There are over 350 species.

Hummingbirds are native to the Americas. They are famous for drinking flower nectar, but also eat a variety of insects for nutrition. Hummingbird feeders must be cleaned regularly (2x week in warm weather) to prevent the growth of a toxic mold which kills the birds.

The Aztec god of war Huitzilopochtli is often depicted as a hummingbird. In Aztec legend, fallen warriors would return to earth as hummingbirds and butterflies.

Not to be confused with [[kingfisher]]s.

title: p-40_warhawk
body:
Built by Curtiss and flown by every Allied country with an air force, the [b]P-40 Warhawk[/b] is one of the most iconic and influential American aircraft ever produced, for both engineering and cultural reasons.

Despite being inferior in speed and altitude performance to most frontline aircraft when the United States entered [[WWII]], the P-40 was famous for punching above its weight. The P-40 was tough, easy to fly and could outdive fighters six years newer and fifteen thousand dollars more expensive - strengths that were exploited by the famous "[[Flying Tigers]]", who exclusively flew P-40s. 

But much more importantly the P-40 was culturally influential. Those Flying Tigers became an important propaganda tool for the United States, and the shark-teeth warpaint that adorned their P-40s had been copied an innumerable amount of times on any aircraft on any country- including, ironically, Japan.

[b]An Old Spider Spins Webs of Memory[/b]
[quote]At least once in their lifetime, a person reflects back on all that might have been...

In the late 19th century, in a city somewhere in Europe, three groups struggle interminably for dominance. The delicate balance of their deadlock maintains peace in the city, but the arrival of three mages, all seeking a most precious treasure, threatens to upend everything...

This is the story of one whose regrets haunt him to this day. What careless mistake does he speak of? What plunged him into a world of remorse and self-recrimination?[/quote]

title: wind_chime
body:
Also called a wind-bell, the wind chime is a decorative object suspended in midair that has three basic forms:
* A cluster of small pieces of metal, glass, pottery, bamboo, seashell, or wood that collide with each other and make noise when blown by the [[wind]]
* A cluster of tubes or rods, often made of metal or wood, that are rung by a central clapper, to which is attached a flat plate to catch the wind
* A single [[bell]] or open-ended glass globe whose clapper is attached to a flat plate to catch the wind. 

h4. See also

h4. External links

title: voices_&_letters_collection!
body:
[b]Valentine's 2019: Voices & Letters Collection! ~Murasaki Shikibu and the Seven Cursed Books~[/b]
[quote]Chaldea's underground library has become a popular gathering spot among the Servants. The library, created by the magical energy of the current librarian, is home to various books from many times and places, and the Servants are drawn to the allure of this treasure trove of texts.

Our tale begins with a single book bathed in the magical energy that slumbers in the library. Why did this book emit a magical light and vanish, only to return as seven accursed books?[/quote]

title: ragnarok_online
body:
A Korean MMORPG based on the manhwa Ragnarok by [[Myung-Jin Lee]], released in 2002 by Gravity Co., Ltd, using the engine from their previous game [[Arcturus]]. Its popularity spawned the anime [[Ragnarok the Animation]]. 

Due to numerous hacks that leaked the source code during the beta years of the game, semi-legal emulated private servers became the most popular way to play for non-East Asian gamers. The game's overall settings and design, particularly its class system, would go on to inspire numerous fantasy MMORPG and media. The franchise itself received several spin-offs and reboots over the years.

Rider-class Servant introduced [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Chocolate River no Sono Saki ni]] event. She was a princess of Aethiopia who was chained to a rock by her parents as a sacrifice to the sea monster [[Cetus (fate)|]], only to be rescued by the hero [[Perseus (fate)|]]. She utilizes the facts that "Andromeda was chained to a rock" and "Cetus was turned to stone" to summon Cetus as her [[Noble Phantasm (fate)|]].

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[lack]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Suzushiro Sayumi]]

title: personality_switch
body:
Post containing characters whose personalities have clearly been switched.

Unlike [[body switch]], characters still keep their true identities (including memories, sense of self, etc) - it's only the personalities (meaning attitude or mannerisms) that are switched.

h4.See also: 

* [[Please Swap these Character Personalities (meme)|]], a pixiv meme which uses a specific template. 
* [[Tag group:Artistic license]]

title: body_switch
body:
When two characters swap bodies.

This means the characters' entire mental identities (including memories, sense of self, etc) have been transferred to the other's body (in contrast to [[personality switch]], where only the personality, meaning attitude and mannerisms, is switched).

There should be some clear indication that the swapping has taken place in the picture or in the commentary, otherwise it's just a [[personality switch]].

A good example is post #4619026.

title: tartaglia_(foul_legacy_transformation)_(genshin_impact)
body:
[[Tartaglia (genshin impact)|]]'s appearance after he activates his foul legacy, a power originating from the Abyss that he learned from [[Skirk (genshin impact)|]]. Appears as the third and final phase of his boss fight. 
He takes a drastically different appearance from his other two outfits, growing a lot larger and wearing black and purple [[armor]] with a long, [[purple cape]]. His [[orange hair]] becomes [[spiked hair|spiky]] and his mask now has long [[red horns]] with a [[one-eyed|singular]] eye in the center.

He now wields the power of his electro [[delusion (genshin impact)|]] and hydro [[vision (genshin impact)|]] at the same time.

title: boots
body:
A type of footwear characterized for their durability. They cover the entire foot as well as the ankle, or even more. They can be made from [[leather]], rubber, or even [[metal]]. Some have steel plating on the end to protect the toes.

Footwear that doesnt cover the whole foot (like [[mary janes]]), footwear that doesn't cover the ankle (like [[oxfords]]), footwear that are less durable (like [[high tops]]) are tagged as [[shoes]].  

So, while high tops cover the ankle, their comparative lack of durability classify them as shoes (most sneakers are made of textiles or soft plastic). 

h4. Examples

* !post #7213982
* !post #4934843

title: santa_costume
body:
A [[Santa Claus]]-themed outfit. This involves prominent use of red fabric with white trim on the edges. As such, many types of clothing can be used in this style - swimsuits, undergarments, outerwear etc. A wide, black belt may be present.

Due to the many variations on this costume in different cultures through history, it should be noted that although red is the most popular color used in "Santa costumes" on Danbooru, it is [i]not the only[/i] color associated with "Santa." See below for alternate tagged colors.

Use the [[Santa hat]] tag when the majority of a character's clothing is not Santa-themed except for the hat.

Images with the actual Santa Claus character should be tagged with [[Santa Claus]].

title: borrowed_clothes
body:
When a character wears an outfit or accessories belonging to another character for some reason other than [[cosplay]] (trying to dress as the other character).

Might apply to [[cosplay]] posts if the borrowed costume is incomplete, or the borrower is wearing it on top of their ordinary costume, or the owner is also shown while not wearing that garment.

Don't add posts if the character canonically wears those borrowed garments at some point of the story, unless the garments or the act of lending/borrowing them is the focus.

title: zyuden_sentai_kyoryuger
body:
Zyuden Sentai Kyoryuger was Toei Company's 37th entry in its long-running [[Super Sentai]] Japanese tokusatsu television series following [[Tokumei Sentai Go-Busters]]. It aired on TV Asahi from February 17, 2013 to February 9, 2014.

In Korea, the Korean dub of Kyoryuger, known as [i]Power Rangers Dino Force[/i] (not to be confused with the Americanized adaptation [[Power Rangers Dino Charge]]), was so popular that it spawned a Korean sequel series, entitled Power Rangers Dino Force Brave, which was then dubbed into Japanese and aired as [i]Zyuden Sentai Kyoryuger Brave[/i].

title: mighty_morphin_power_rangers
body:
The first series in Saban's [[Power Rangers]] franchise. Largely adapts stock footage from [[Kyouryuu Sentai Zyuranger]] (along with newly filmed footage, often referred to as "Zyu2":[https://www.grnrngr.com/zyu2/]), with elements from [[Gosei Sentai Dairanger]] and [[Ninja Sentai Kakuranger]] being used for the second and third seasons respectively. The third season would also feature a crossover with [[Saban's Masked Rider]], serving as a quasi-backdoor pilot crossover for that show. 

[[Mighty Morphin Alien Rangers]], which used footage from Ninja Sentai Kakuranger along with newly filmed footage, followed after its third season, and directly continues from its events; as a result, it is officially considered 'Season 3.5', with [[Power Rangers Zeo]] being the first full series after Mighty Morphin and Alien Rangers.

Alongside the Zyuranger and Kakuranger suits used, it also debuted the first original Ranger suits in the form of the Dark Rangers from the second season and the Ninja Rangers from the third, the latter based on the costumes used for the Ninjetti-powered Rangers in [[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: The Movie|The Movie]].

title: amesuku_gyaru
body:
A type of [[kogal]] taken to the extreme: [[school uniform]]s characterized by [[tied shirt|tied]] [[open shirt]]s (exposing not just the [[midriff]], but the chest as well, showing off the [[bra]]/[[bikini]] underneath), and a short-enough [[skirt]] that [[panties]] may be [[pantyshot|revealed]], emphasizing the wearer's body. Paired with these are accessories and make-up.

Referred to as "American School" (or Amesuku) style in Japanese, based on what the Japanese think American girls would wear in high school, bolstered by gravure and AVs featuring the attire (potentially inspired by the outfit [[Britney Spears]] wore in "[[...Baby One More Time]]").

title: elise_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Elise[/b] (エリーゼ Erize) is a playable character in [i][[Fire Emblem Fates]][/i].

The youngest child of the Nohrian royal family. Elise displays a naive and childish personality, treating her immediate family with generous love and consideration. However, she is deceptively sharp, being able to sometimes see truths that others may miss. Along with the other royal siblings, she was subject to the family's "concubine wars" at a young age. She is said to be the best at remembering birthdays, and her birthday is on March 19th.

She is voiced by [[Suwa Ayaka]] in Japanese and "Natalie Lander":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natalie_Lander in English.

[b]Starting Class:[/b] Troubadour

title: cthulhu_mythos
body:
This tag is applied to all about "Cthulhu Mythos" by [[H P Lovecraft|H. P. Lovecraft]] and his works.

Lovecraft's guiding aesthetic and philosophical principle was what he termed "cosmicism" or "cosmic horror", the idea that life is incomprehensible to human minds and that the universe is fundamentally inimical to the interests of humankind. As such, his stories express a profound indifference to human beliefs and affairs. 

His "Cthulhu Mythos" is well-known throughout the world. "[[Call of Cthulhu]]", a horror fiction role-playing game was named after his horror stories.

title: callsign:_cedar
body:
A Chinese real-time tactical RPG developed by 礼炮八号设计局 (Salyut 8 Design Bureau) and published by 霍尔果斯纳罗达网络科技有限公司 (Narodnaya Games). Its title (《雪松》 / Позывной: Кедр / Pozyvnoy: Kedr) can also be rendered as Codename: Cedar, and is otherwise just referred to as Cedar in Chinese.

Set in an alternate future, the game takes place on Nox, a beastfolk-inhabited alien moon rapidly industrialized by two rival Earth blocs: the socialist Alliance and the capitalist Entente (paralleling the Cold War). After the Alliance collapses under the strain of the space race, Earth falls into chaos and Nox's fragile modernity begins to decay.

The player is a young veteran, sent to Nox to recover lost Alliance EGO research; mysterious powers native to the planet.

title: mp18
body:
The [b]MP18[/b] ([i]Maschinenpistole 18[/i]) is a [[gun|firearm]] designed by "Hugo Schmeisser":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugo_Schmeisser, the very first open-bolt [b][[submachine gun]][/b] ever. Predominantly chambered in 9×19mm round, it was introduced in 1918 by the Imperial German Army during World War I as the primary [[weapon]] of the "Stormtroopers":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stormtroopers_(Imperial_Germany). Its design became the basis for most of european SMGs manufactured between 1920 and 1960.

Unlike more modern SMGs, the MP18 featured a wooden rifle-styled buttstock without pistol grip, and relatively heavy due to thick milled receiver tube. Magazine is inserted on the left, and can accept the 32-round "snail" [[drum magazine]] designed for the [[luger p08|Artillery Luger]].

h4. See also

* [[List of weapons]]
* [[MP28]]

h4. External links

* Wikipedia: "MP18":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MP_18

title: mg34
body:
The [B]MG34[/b] is a 7.92×57mm Mauser [[ammunition belt|belt-fed]] [b][[machine gun]][/b] used by Nazi Germany before and during [[World War II]]. Introduced in 1934, it was considered the first [[machine gun]]. It features a quick-change barrel, a tubular [[barrel shroud]] with circular perforation, a [[bipod]], conical [[muzzle device]] and [[flip-up sight|flip-up iron sights]].
The MG34 was not suitable for quick mass production and costly. So it was supplanted by the [[MG42]] despite both remained in service.

h4. See also

* [[List of Weapons]]
* [[MG34 (Girls' Frontline)]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: MG34":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MG_34

title: m1917_enfield
body:
The [b]M1917 Enfield[/b] (United States Rifle, cal .30, Model of 1917) is an [[united states|American]] modification and production of the [[P14 Enfield]] [[bolt action]] [b][[rifle]][/b], which was developed and manufactured during 1917–1918. It was used by the U.S. [[military]], mainly during the [[World War I]] (The M1917 became the most common American weapon on the Western Front, as there was limited numbers of [[M1903 Springfield]] to only supplement the existing supply of rifles) and [[World War II]] (for rear-line usage and as a lend-lease weapon for allied countries.). Its' feed system is an 6 .30-06 [[ammunition|rounds]] internal [[magazine (weapon)|magazine]], loaded with a [[clip (weapon)|clip]].

One distinguishing visual feature from the [[united kingdom|British]] counterpart is a longer and more prominent indentation on the fore-end. 

h4. See also

* [[Lee-Enfield]]
* [[List of weapons]]


h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: M1917 Enfield":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M1917_Enfield

title: smash_invitation
body:
An item associated with the [i][[Super  Smash Bros.]][/i] franchise. It is simply a white [[letter]] with the [[Super Smash Bros. logo]] as a red [[wax seal]].

It originally appeared in the first trailer for [i]Super Smash Bros. for WiiU/Nintendo 3DS[/i] as a letter of invitation only extended to the [[villager (animal crossing)|Villager]] of [i][[Animal Crossing]][/i], as a play on that game's letter system.  Thanks to fan popularity, the invitation was used in association with other hopefuls and eventual roster entries.

title: ratoratah_(ooo_combo)
body:
One of [[Kamen Rider OOO]]'s combos, accessed via the [[Lion]], [[Tiger]] (Tora), and [[Cheetah]] [[Core Medal|Core Medals]].

OOO can dazzle his enemies by diffusing light with Lion Head's [[mane]], which is intense enough to incinerate, and run like the [[wind]] with the Cheetah Legs.

His Scanning Charge is the [b]Gush Cross[/b], which projects three yellow rings in front of OOO before charging through them with the Cheetah Medal's speed before delievering a cross slash on the target with the Tora Claws infused with the Lion Medal's energy projection. 
Also, as an ability exclusive to this form, it is possible to emit an high-heat light called the [b]Liodias[/b] from its entire body.

title: ariake_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Ariake[/i]. Character design by [[Kujou Ichiso]]. 

She has [[long_hair|long]] dark [[purple hair]] with an [[orange_hair|orange]] [[gradient_hair|gradient end]], tied into a [[low ponytail]] with [[bangs]] and [[hair_over_one_eye|covering her left eye]], and [[purple eyes]]. Her default outfit is shared with her sister Yuugure: a [[black hat|black]] [[beret]], a [[white shirt|white undershirt]] paired with a [[double-breasted]] [[black shirt|black]] [[dress shirt]], [[black jacket]], [[grey skirt]], [[black socks]], and [[black footwear|black shoes]]. 

Her [[rigging]] is composed of her funnel and foremast to her back with 61 cm quad [[torpedo tubes]] on the sides, a 12.7 twin [[handgun]] mount, and [[depth charge]]s on her left [[thigh strap]].

title: heywood_l._edwards_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the USS [i]Heywood L. Edwards[/i] (DD-663), named for the captain of the American destroyer USS [i]Reuben James[/i], the first American vessel sunk during [[World War II]]. After the war, the [i]Edwards[/i] was transferred to the new [[Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force]], where she was given the name [i]Ariake[/i]. She spent the rest of her career with the Japanese, being decommissioned in 1974 and scrapped in 1976. Character design by [[Zeco]], she was originally revealed in C2 Kikan's Comiket 101 booth. She became a playable character with the Winter 2023 event in March 2023.

In Kancolle, Edwards has long, [[grey hair]] with a notable [[ahoge]] and [[glasses]] over her [[blue eyes]]. Her clothing consists of a [[white hat]], [[white gloves]], [[black thighhighs]], a [[black skirt]], and an off-shoulder [[serafuku]] with a [[black sailor collar]]. Her shirt is initially colored grey, but becomes a [[blue shirt]] like her sisters at Kai. A blue [[armband]] on her right arm displays her historical emblem beneath her full name and hull number. 

Her [[rigging]] is standard for the Fletcher class: [[rudder footwear]], hull portions on her sides with depth charges, and a larger section attached to her back with gun mounts, [[smokestack]]s, and [[anti-aircraft gun]]s. An additional gun mount is carried as a firearm in her hands. At base level, the anti-aircraft guns on Edwards' rigging are single-barrel [[Bofors 40 mm Gun]]s, while at Kai they change to double-barrel. The coloration of Heywood's rigging also changes: from camouflage at Base to "Measure 22":[https://www.shipcamouflage.com/measure_22.htm] at Kai.

title: kioh_gyoku
body:
Kioh Gyoku (稀翁玉, lit. "Rare Venerable Orb") is a vertical-scrolling danmaku shoot 'em up, and is the second official game in the [[Seihou|Seihou Project]] by "Shunsatsu sare do?" (at time part of Amusement Makers). It was released specifically for the Windows operating system around December time in 2001. It is a unique game where two players indirectly battle one another by charging and releasing charge attacks and bombs upon the other player, similar in the style of [[Phantasmagoria of Dim.Dream]].

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Kioh_Gyoku

title: samidare_(rebrank)
body:
Samidare (五月雨, romanized Samidare, meaning Early Summer Rain) is a shooting game from Amusement Makers / Project Blank(P.N.B) (RebRank). It is a [[danmaku]] game with shields and is perhaps Amusement Makers' most well-known work in the West. As a RebRank game, it is neither a [[Touhou]] game, nor a [[Seihou]] game. However, it pays homage to both with elements such as the in-game history and the extra stage.

Samidare takes place on and around the Earth in the 30th century. 

https://touhou.fandom.com/wiki/Samidare

title: fletcher_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of "USS [i]Fletcher[/i] (hull number DD-445)":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS_Fletcher_(DD-445)], nameship of the US Navy's 175 Fletcher-class destroyers. Her namesake (and namesake of the class) is Navy Admiral "Frank Friday Fletcher (1855-1928)":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Friday_Fletcher], who served in the 19th and 20th centuries, most notably as commander of naval forces at the "Battle of Veracruz":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_occupation_of_Veracruz] in Mexico. She is designed by [[Zeco]], who also illustrated the first of her class in the game, [[johnston (kancolle)|Johnston]].

The Fletcher class was the most numerous of the destroyers that participated in World War II, built completely free from any treaty restrictions with a larger size, larger fuel capacity and range, and better armaments. In the world of Kantai Collection, this translates to Fletcher and Johnston being tall and having ample bustlines; among the other non-Japanese destroyers before them, only [[tashkent (kancolle)|Tashkent]] is comparable in those areas while the others are implied to have flat chests.

Being the nameship of the class, Fletcher herself is given traits of [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] with triangular [[double bun|side buns]], [[purple eyes]], and a [[large breasts|very well-endowed]] body. Her outfit is similar to Johnston's but with the black features being given lighter colors: a stylized [[serafuku]] which consists of an [[off shoulder|off-shoulder]] [[blue shirt]] with a [[white sailor collar]] that exposes her [[cleavage]], a [[yellow neckerchief]], and a short [[white skirt|white]] [[pleated skirt]], along with [[white thighhighs]] that are shielded by what seem to be metallic thigh and [[shin guards]] and red [[rudder footwear|rudder shoes]]. She also wears [[white gloves|white short gloves]] and a metallic [[hairband]]. In her remodeled form, she adds a [[star hair ornament]] to each side of her hairband.

Her [[rigging]] consists of two [[smokestack]]s and two 5-inch [[cannon]] [[ship turret]]s with one set on each side of her rigging. Her hull number is emblazoned on each side of her lower rigs. She also carries a [[cargo net]], a reference to her rescuing many survivors of the USS [i][[Northampton (kancolle)|]][/i] during the "Battle of Tassafaronga":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Tassafaronga] by using cork-floated cargo nets.

On her [[Fletcher Kai (kancolle)|Kai remodel]], Fletcher gains a silver [[star hair ornament]] on each side of her hairband, and her rigging gains an additional radar set atop the director and loses its blue camoflage in favor of standard grey color.

Fletcher is the first non-Japanese destroyer in the game to get a second remodel, and winds up with [i]two[/i] [[Fletcher Mk II (kancolle)|reversible modes]]. In both of them, she loses the cargo net and gains a pair of [[headphones]]. One of the modes gives her a quintuple torpedo launcher to carry, while the other completely redoes her rigging, giving her experimental ASW equipment to carry, making her headband more angular (mimicking the changed shape of her bridge), and changing the color of her skirt and thighhighs from white to black.

title: sasaki_kojirou_(fate)
body:
[[Fate (series)|Fate series]] character. An Assassin-class Servant who appears in [[Fate/stay night]] and [[Fate/Grand Order]].

He has [[blue eyes]] and [[blue hair]] tied into a [[ponytail]]. He is often seen wearing [[Japanese clothes]] and wielding a [[sword]].

In [[Fate/stay night]], he is a Servant summoned by [[Medea (caster) (fate)|]], another Servant, which is normally against the rules of the Holy Grail War. This makes him weaker than a normal Servant and dependent on Caster for mana. In the [[Heaven's Feel]] route, he is killed and his body is used to summon [[Hassan of the Cursed Arm (Fate)|]], the True Assassin.

title: hassan_of_the_cursed_arm_(fate)
body:
[[Fate (series)|Fate series]] character. He appears in [[Fate/stay night]], where he is known as [b]True Assassin[/b], and in [[Fate/Grand Order]], where is he known as [b]Hassan of the Cursed Arm[/b].

His appearance is that of a slender, dark man with a [[skull mask]] and his oversized right arm wrapped in [[bandages]].

In [[Fate/stay night]], he appears in the [[Heaven's Feel]] route as the Servant of [[Matou Zouken]].

[b]True Name:[/b] Hassan of the Cursed Arm, one of nineteen people to hold the title of Hassan-i-Sabbah.
[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]
[b]Illustrator:[/b] [[Task Owner]] ([[Fate/Grand Order]])
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Inada Tetsu]]

title: cigarette_receptacle
body:
A cigarette receptacle is a container or device for extinguishing and disposing of cigarette waste. Originally provided as a courtesy to smokers in public places, cigarette receptacles are now commonplace as smoking bans and designated smoking areas require proper disposal methods.

Not to be confused with [[ashtray]].

title: rain_world
body:
Rain World is a unforgiving survival platform game, featuring breath-taking pixel art scenery. The player takes the role of a creature called a [[slugcat]] trying to survive in an alien, post-apocalyptic ecosystem. It was developed by Videocult and published by Adult Swim Games and Akupara Games in 2017.


h4. External links

* "Official website":[https://rainworldgame.com/]

title: prinz_eugen_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the German heavy cruiser [i]Prinz Eugen[/i] in [[Azur Lane]]. Designed by [[Realmbw]], voiced by [[Sakura Ayane]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair|white]], [[grey hair|grey]], or [[aqua hair]] tied up in a [[two side up]] and with a small red highlight. Her eyes are [[orange eyes|orange]]. Her outfit is a grey and red [[double-breasted]] dress with [[long sleeves]] and a notable [[side cutout]] showing her [[armpits]] and [[sideboob]], and also that she has a [[mole_on_breast|mole on her right breast]]. There are several [[iron cross|iron crosses]] adorning her outfit near the collar and on her sleeves. She wears [[black thighhighs]] with [[garter straps]]. Prinz Eugen also lacks a skirt of any sort, with her [[panties]] readily exposed.

title: edward_newgate
body:
A major character of the manga and anime [[One Piece]]. [b]Whitebeard[/b] is the captain of the [[Whitebeard Pirates]], one of the Four Emperors, the rival and friend of the late Pirate King [[Gol D. Roger]], and known as the strongest man in the world.

Having consumed the Gura Gura no Mi [[Devil Fruit]], he has the power to create shockwaves, spawning earthquakes and tsunamis, and even "cracking" the air itself.

[spoiler]In the battle at [[Marineford]], he was killed by [[Marshall D. Teach|"Blackbeard"]], who took his power and title for himself.[/spoiler]

h4. See also

* [[The One Piece is real (meme)]]

title: william_d._porter_(azur_lane)
body:
USS William D. Porter was a Fletcher-class destroyer serving in the US Navy during WWII. She is, infamously, the "unluckiest ship of WWII". 

Her bad luck streak began when President Roosevelt, relaxing in an easy chair upon the deck of the USS Iowa, was watching an exercise that Willie Dee was a part of and Willie Dee accidentally launched a live torpedo at the USS Iowa to which the USS Iowa only barely outmaneuvered. The sailor who accidentally fired the torpedo was thrown into the brig but Roosevelt immediately pardoned him so he could get back to his duties. 

While this particular event was only the start of her ill fortune, said ill fortune apexed dramatically at her end. A Japanese kamikaze barely missed hitting the Willie Dee during the final days of the conflict, hitting the water before colliding with the ship. The momentum of the kamikaze plane, carrying a torpedo, sent the submerged plane and its now deceased pilot directly underneath the Willie Dee, where the torpedo then activated and exploded, bifurcating her and sending her under. 

Willie Dee has been with Azur Lane since the game started, but only as a loading graphic and as a temporary placeholder for other ships and the only official artwork of her is in the background of image of the other Fletchers. She has (as of April 2025) yet to be released to the player as an actual ship.

title: atf
body:
The Bureau of [b]A[/b]lcohol, [b]T[/b]obacco, [b]F[/b]irearms and Explosives (BATFE) is a domestic law enforcement agency within the [[United States|US]] Department of Justice. Its responsibilities include the investigation and prevention of the unlawful use, manufacture, and possession of [[gun|firearms]] and [[explosive]]s; acts of [[arson]] and [[bomb]]ings; including illegal trafficking of [[alcohol]] and [[tobacco]] products.

Sometimes humorously referred to as AFT after a certain US president referred to ATF as "the AFT" multiple times.

Not to be confused with [[All The Fallen]], a community for loli/shota fans.

h1. External links
* "Official website":https://www.atf.gov
* "Wikipedia: Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bureau_of_Alcohol,_Tobacco,_Firearms_and_Explosives

title: repair_bucket
body:
An item in Kantai Collection. Appears as a green [[bucket]] with "修復" ([i]shufuku[/i], "recovery material") printed on it.

Its main function is to repair ships instantly. For new admirals, this equipment is rarely used or needed, but to experienced ones, it's vital equipment for ships like battleships and aircraft carriers which have ungodly long repair times that often range from hours to even days.

It is unknown exactly what's inside the bucket, though in the anime it's a magical liquid that can cause a ship girl to experience intense pleasure as a side effect of its use.

The tag can be used on containers [i]based[/i] on the repair bucket (e.g. as a [[drinking glass]] on post #2453713 and as an [[ice cream]] tub on post #2364987) as it is not currently implicated to "[[bucket]]". (see topic #13619)

title: female_corrin_(novice_vacationer)_(fire_emblem)
body:
Tag used for [[female corrin (fire emblem)|Female Corrin]] from [[Fire Emblem Fates]] when dressed in her summer attire from [[Fire_Emblem_Heroes]]' 2017 "Nohrian Summer":[https://feheroes.fandom.com/wiki/Nohrian_Summer_(Focus)] banner. 

The Corrin unit using this outfit is officially known as [i]Corrin: Novice Vacationer[/i]

Can typically be identified thanks to the outfit's characteristics: a [[white_bikini]] with a [[front-tie top]] and a [[microskirt]] that's a [[bikini skirt]], a [[thigh strap]] that like the skirt has a [[black bow]], an [[anklet]] with a flower, a [[flower necklace]], and a black [[hairband]] with a purple [[hair flower]]. As is typical of Corrin, she is of course [[barefoot]].

Likely to include her weapon from the game, a blue picture [[book]] with marine life on the cover.

Note that it's possible (especially in older artwork) to depict Female Corrin in a swimsuit, without it being the one described above, in which case this tag should not be used.

title: female_corrin_(nohr_noble)_(fire_emblem)
body:
Design of [[Female corrin (fire emblem)|Female Corrin]]'s Nohr Noble Class, the promoted class associated with the "Nohr" side of [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Compared with Female Corrin's regular design, Nohr Noble features black becoming the outfit's most prominent color, Nohr Noble is also notable for now having [[cleavage]], and removing the [[kusazuri]]-like piece on her thigh, exposing her thighs from both the front and the back, making the outfit overall a lot more revealing.

title: daisy_(flower)
body:
Daisy and aster are blanket names for many similar looking [[flower|flowers]] in the expansive [i]Asteraceae[/i] family. Asters are practically indistinguishable from daisies for tagging purposes.

Daisies and asters typically have a spiky-looking head made up of tiny disc florets surrounded by a multitude of long petals. Gerber daisies will also have an inner ring of ray florets around the center head.

Common daisy colors include white petals with a yellow or orange center and yellow petals with a dark brown center, but daisies & asters can come in practically [b]any[/b] color.

For tagging purposes, limit this tag to flowers that look generally like a Common Daisy, a Black-Eyed Susan, a Gerber Daisy, asters, or any color variation on that basic design.

h4. Other distinctive flowers in [i]Asteraceae[/i]

* [[Chamomile]]
* [[Chicory (flower)|]]
* [[Chrysanthemum]]
* [[Cornflower]]

When transformed into this form, she has [[long hair|longer]] [[two side up]] with [[glowing hair|glowing tips]], along with a [[long braid]] in the center back of her hair. title: icarus_(seihou)
body: Icarus (イカロス Ikarosu) appears to be a really powerful being who seems to fight in flesh without a machine, which is something strange for a Seihou Project character. She's the final boss of a boss rush in the Extra Stage in [[Banshiryuu]], but because there is no story to the Extra stage, information about Icarus is a complete mystery. Her only line is "I'm the last boss, I'm strong!" which breaks the fourth wall.

title: seihou
body:
"西方" (Japanese for "west") 

A series of doujin vertical shooter games created by the members of "Shunsatsu sare do?", featuring futuristic themes with science. It's currently no longer produced, with "Ponchi/PBG":https://twitter.com/pbghogehoge and co. instead currently working on "[i]SUPER Mate Mate Laser[/i]":[https://ss-do.sakura.ne.jp/#/games/smml].

It's known among groups that Seihou is a "sister series" to the [[Touhou]] Project due to being its opposite conceptually, right down to its name, Seihou, meaning "western", as opposed to Touhou, which means "eastern". [[ZUN (artist)|]] has contributed music to the series, and three Touhou characters also appear in Seihou as guests. 

[[Samidare (rebrank)|]] is neither a Seihou nor Touhou game, but rather a Project Blank game. However, it contains elements of each and both Seihou and Touhou characters appear in it. It was created by the members of RebRank, who, just like "Shunsatsu sare do?" and Team Shanghai Alice, branched from Amusement Makers.

h4. Games

* 秋霜玉 ([[Shuusou Gyoku]]) - "source code":[https://ss-do.sakura.ne.jp/#/diary/93] released c. early February 2019
* 稀翁玉 ([[Kioh Gyoku]])
* 幡紫竜 ([[Banshiryuu]])

title: ilia_(seihou)
body:
The Tri Stars are a group of sisters called [[Tolia (Seihou)|]] (トリア toria), Ilia (イリア iria) and [[Felia_(Seihou)|]] (フェリア feria) and are the third stage boss of [[Banshiryuu]]. It's unknown who's the older and younger one between Tolia and Ilia, but Felia is the youngest among them. Tolia is smart (but a coward if she isn't protected), Ilia is a scientist and Felia bluffs when she says she can see the future.

During the scenario, they have a warp device that allows people to teleport them. The heroine wishes to use this in order to easily get to Mars, but they won't allow them unless they rented, so they end up fighting. After their defeat, they send them to an unusual place, where they meet [[VIVIT-r]] or [[Sakurasaki Hirano|Hirano Sakurasaki]], depending on the player's character. On the later versions of the game, the battle ends with a huge explosion. 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/The_Tri_Stars

title: lagunas
body:
Lagunas (ラグナス Ragunasu) is the younger brother of [[Yuitia_(seihou)|]] and the fifth boss and sixth midboss of [[Banshiryuu]]. He refused anyone to enter RedStorm on Mars as Yuitia was fused with a machine in RedStorm, which cause machinery to go on a rampage. He was trying to protect her, aware that Yuitia was the cause of the incident. He was worried that the heroine was going to "get rid of her" instead of leaving her in pain, so he refused anyone to go near her and he'll fight them. He has [[Kirishima_Yuuta|Yuuta Kirishima]] working for him. 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Lagunas

title: io_(granblue_fantasy)
body:
[i][[Granblue Fantasy]][/i] character.

One of the main supporting characters in the main story. A [[magical girl]] with [[long hair|long]], [[twintails|twintailed]], and mainly [[blonde hair]] that [[gradient hair|gradients]] into [[rainbow hair|various colors]] and [[blue eyes]]. She wears a dress, black thighhighs, and crystal-like ornaments in her hair. Her in-game art as a character has her complexion as a [[dark skin|dark]] ruddy color, though a majority of her appearances in the "official 4koma":[/pools/9960] depicts her with average Caucasian skin. However her recent 4koma appearances has her skin tone closer to the original art.

She was given a SSR version during the summer beach festival event; where she wears a frilly white bikini and flowers replace both her staff and crystal-like hair ornaments.

title: banshiryuu
body:
Banshiryuu (幡紫竜, lit. "Pennant Purple Dragon") is a vertical-scrolling danmaku shoot 'em up that focuses on fewer, faster bullets, and is the third official game in the [[Seihou]] Project by "Shunsatsu sare do?". The game came in two major versions, released at Comiket 67 (Winter 2004) and Comiket 74 (Summer 2008) respectively. Both versions were released specifically for the Windows operating system. 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Banshiryuu

title: yuitia_(seihou)
body:
Yuitia (ユイティア) is [[Lagunas]]' older sister and a phantom. She is the final boss of [[Banshiryuu]]. 

Yuitia died 11 years ago near Mars due a spaceship accident where she was along all that time. However, at the exact time of the accident, the sleeping soul of Yuitia did not at all notice her own death and continued to wander, which made her become a phantom. Yuitia was lost in her own existence. She didn't know who she was and what she is. Sometime later, she was taken into and fused with RedStorm (which lost her true character) and went on a rampage as well as causing a rampage among all the machines that used RedStorm. She was later rescued by [[VIVIT-r]] and [[sakurasaki_hirano| Hirano Sakurasaki]] where put a stop to the rampage. Yuitia was thankful for been release. After 11 years has went by, Yuitia did not understand the flow of time at all and was confused upon meeting Lagunas and seeing that he has grown big.

Said in her profile, her personality changes when she wears different clothes. In the dialogues of both C67 and C74 versions, she was speaking in katakana.

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Yuitia

title: kirishima_yuuta
body:
Yuuta Kirishima (桐島 雄太 Kirishima Yuuta) is a subordinate for [[Lagunas]], the Stage 2 boss and Stage 5 midboss/supporting boss of [[Banshiryuu]]. He uses a flying [[tank]] in battle, and in the C74 version, he uniquely used an "earth destruction bomb" that would result in an immediate game over if destroyed.

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Yuuta_Kirishima

title: vivit-r
body:
VIVIT-r is a maid-type android from the future and the heroine of [[Banshiryuu]], being a playable character. In her official profile, she was described to have "considerably more twisted personality than even the Vivit of old eras" and earlier in the Seihou Project, there was a maid-type android called [[VIVIT]]. For VIVIT-r, it's unknown if she's powered by cactus energy and unlike VIVIT, she doesn't need a broom to fly, but she's run by the energy source device called "RedStorm" discovered by [[Erich_(Seihou)|]].

h4. External links

* "VIVIT-r on Touhou Wiki":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/VIVIT-r

title: muse_(seihou)
body:
Muse (ミューズ Myuuzu) is known as the fusion of science and magic, the Clan leader who dreams of merging magic with modern science. She's a master of alchemy, so she can manipulate any type of matter into whatever form, shape, or composition she wishes. A master puppeteer, she uses her puppets as weapons and is extremely proficient with them. She also has complete mastery over the art of throwing crosses (not knives). 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Muse_(Seihou_Character)

title: morgan_(seihou)
body:
Morgan (モーガン Mōgan) is a "self-proclaimed", "so-called genius-type female" and a bit of a mad scientist at times. Apparently, she's an important character, but has no background story. She appears as the 4th boss of [[Kioh Gyoku]], then about 7 years later when [[Banshiryuu]] had C74 version release, she appeared as the 5th Extra Stage boss as part of a boss rush. 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Morgan

title: erich_(seihou)
body:
Erich (エーリッヒ Ērihhi) is a 62-year-old scientist who is the chairman and founder of the Cactus Company, the company that discovered and perfected cactus energy. He has had many achievements, and is considerably well-known in the world of [[Seihou]] since he also discovered and developed RedStorm. However, his personality has just a little tendency to be eccentric. He was part of a disastrous accident 30 years ago caused by cactus energy, and due to this accident, he had to become a cyborg. His daughter [[vivit_(erich's_daughter)| Vivit]] also became captive in the "Other Dimension". 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Erich

title: marie_(seihou)
body:
Marie (マリー Marī) is a 19-year-old lady and is the Lady of a benefactor known as the "Industry". Although she can be whimsical at times and is a little sadistic, she garners the respect of anyone put under her command nonetheless. She appears in all of the [[Seihou]] Project games. 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Marie

title: gates_(seihou)
body:
Gates (ゲイツ Geitsu) is a hot-blooded 45-year-old military commanding officer. He's currently in charge of keeping an eye on [[Erich_(Seihou)|Erich's]] private army on behalf of the Earth's military, but he sometimes works on Erich's behalf. He has showed up in all three [[Seihou]] Project games.

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Gates

title: milia_(seihou)
body:
Milia (ミリア) is a subordinate commander and a researcher of the Cactus Company hired by Erich from the outskirts. She is also known as "Lightning-fast Milia" and has appeared in every game so far in the [[Seihou]] Project. 

https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Milia

body:

body:

title: tribe_nine
body:
A Japanese multimedia franchise created by Too Kyo Games, under the direction of Kodaka Kazutaka (who also created [[Danganronpa (series)|]] under Spike Chunsoft), and Akatsuki. It consists of an anime of the same name produced by Liden Films that aired between January-March 2022, a webtoon series with the subtitle "War of Tokyo"[tn](トライブナイン/ウォー・オブ・トーキョー)[/tn] that ran between December 2022 up to sometime in 2023, and an action role-playing gacha game first announced in 2020 and officially released globally on February 20, 2025 for mobile and PC via Steam.

The anime mainly followed the stories of the rebellious Tribes and their many battles, with Extreme Baseball (XB) as the battleground, in the cyberpunk mega-city of Neo Tokyo.

The game is set around two years after the events of the anime, mainly following amnesiac aspiring XB player [[Kuronaka Yo]] and his team, the Trash Tribe, as they battle against Neo Tokyo's newest and most dangerous tyrant [[Zero (Tribe Nine)|Zero]], as well as nine other dangerous individuals called NUMBERS, in both his "favorite" death games called Extreme Games (XG) and in XB, in order to free Neo Tokyo from his clutches.

h4. Characters
* [[Akiba Hinagiku]]
* [[Arisugawa Saori]]
* [[Iroha Tsuki]]
* [[Semba Tsuruko]]

title: tadokoro_akira
body:
One of the main characters in [[Live A Live]] and main protagonist of The Near Future: The Outsider chapter. A psychic teenage punk who sells taiyaki and also happens to end up driving a massive robot.

[spoilers]He is one of the 8 selectable main protagonists for the Final Chapter: The Dominion of Hate. If others are selected (except for Oersted), he can be recruited as a member of the selected protagonist's party.[/spoilers]

He is voiced by [[Akabane Kenji]] and [[Mikami Shiori]] in the 2022 remake.

title: pogo_(live_a_live)
body:
One of the main characters in [[Live A Live]] and main protagonist of the Prehistory: The First chapter. A young and excitable caveman who learns much more of the world he lives in.

[spoilers]He is one of the 8 selectable main protagonists for the Final Chapter: The Dominion of Hate. If others are selected (except for Oersted), he can be recruited as a member of the selected protagonist's party. Can be recruited without fighting if [[Lei Kuugo]] is the selected protagonist.[/spoilers]

He is voiced by [[Ogata Megumi]] in the 2022 remake.

title: oboro-maru_(live_a_live)
body:
One of the main characters in [[Live A Live]] and main protagonist of the Twilight of Edo Japan: The Infiltrator chapter. A young shinobi of the Enma Clan, sent on an important mission to rescue a [[sakamoto ryouma (live a live)|prisoner]] from the clutches of [[Ode Iou]], for the sake of Japan's future.

[spoilers]He is one of the 8 selectable main protagonists for the Final Chapter: The Dominion of Hate. If others are selected (except for Oersted), he can be recruited as a member of the selected protagonist's party after fighting him.[/spoilers]

He is voiced by Hashizume Tomohisa in the 2022 remake.

title: eyebrows
body:
Most characters on danbooru have eyebrows. Use a better tag for unusual eyebrows instead, such as:

h3. Type of eyebrows

h5. Expressing emotion

* !post #3333779: [[Raised eyebrows]], eyebrows are elevated from the usual resting position.
* !post #7355993: [[Raised eyebrow]], for when one eyebrow is raised but the other is not.
* !post #2366353: [[Cocked eyebrow]], for when one eyebrow is raised and the other is lowered.
* !post #5726330: [[Raised inner eyebrows]], eyebrows with only the inner ends raised. Often an expression of [[smug]]ness or [[fear]].
* !post #7854327: [[Furrowed brow]], when the skin around the eyebrows becomes creased.
* !post #1871573: [[V-shaped eyebrows]], slanted inwards, forming a V shape.

h5. Sizes and shapes

* !post #5636658: [[Short eyebrows]], for unusually short eyebrows that only partially cover the brow ridges.
* !post #8002642: [[Thick eyebrows]], for unusually thick cases.
* !post #8041159: [[Huge eyebrows]], for when the eyebrow is thicker than thick.
* !post #1750845: [[Long eyebrows]], for unusually long eyebrows.
* !post #6305260: [[Unibrow]], eyebrows that are connected together.
* !post #8034214: [[Forked eyebrows]], for eyebrows that are split at the outer ends.
* !post #5906879: [[Curly eyebrows]], eyebrows that curl.
* !post #7531006: [[Hikimayu]], shaving off the eyebrows and painting new ones. Often in a distinctive comma shape or in a trapezoidal shape.
* !post #5499154: [[Eyebrow piercing]], a piercing though the eyebrow.
* !post #8775653: [[Eyebrow cut]], a grooming style where one or more thin vertical stripes are shaved from one or both eyebrows.
* !post #7092324: [[Scar across eyebrow]]

h5. In relation to hair

* !post #7427607: [[Eyebrows hidden by hair]], eyebrows that are hidden behind bangs but are still visible.
* !post #7957120: [[Mismatched eyebrows]], for when the eyebrows are a different color than the character's hair.

h5. Other

* [[no_eyebrows]]

title: doven_wolf
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series.

[b]AMX-014 Döven Wolf[/b]

A revolutionary unit developed by [[Haman Karn]]'s [[Neo Zeon]] from a captured Federation [[Gundam Mk V]] prototype MS. It is loaded with a massively powerful reactor, a huge mega-launcher rivaling even the [[zz_gundam|Double Zeta Gundam]]'s high-mega Cannon, [[incom_(gundam)|INCOMs]] and a quasi-psycommu system which allowed even non-Newtypes to execute the deadly all-range attack. All at the cost of less armor.

A few units ended up in the hands of the [[Earth Federation]] after the [[gundam_zz|First Neo Zeon War]], where they were converted into the [b][[silver_bullet_(mobile_suit)|ARX-014 Silver Bullet]][/b] for testing and evaluation, and many others found themselves in the hands of the Sleeves, painted in their traditional markings.

It was [[Rakan Dahkaran]]'s final mecha of choice.

title: smith_&_wesson_sw
body:
The Smith & Wesson SW, better known as the Smith & Wesson Sigma, is a polymer-frame [[handgun]] designed by [[Smith & Wesson]]. The Sigma series of pistols were Smith & Wesson's first handguns to utilize a polymer frame construction. Additionally, the Sigma was one of the first pistols specifically designed to utilize the .40 S&W cartridge, though 9x19 Parabellum versions were also available.

The Sigma has a rocky history, due to its design being very similar to a [[Glock]] in design and operation. This led to Glock suing Smith & Wesson for patent infringement, which resulted in Smith & Wesson having to alter the design and pay an undisclosed settlement to Glock.

h4. See Also
"Smith & Wesson SW: Wikipedia":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smith_%26_Wesson_SW]

title: gone_with_the_wind
body:
[I]Gone With the Wind[/i] is a 1939 historical romance film based on the 1936 novel of the same name by author Margaret Mitchell, focused on a plantation in the American state of Georgia before, during, and after the [[American Civil War]]. 

Aside from it's success domestically and in other international audiences, the film was a smash hit upon its 1952 release in Japan largely due to its focus in the latter half on picking up one's lives after war has claimed everything else. Main character [[Scarlett O'Hara]]'s closing line, "Tomorrow is another day", resonated particularly to a nation that was itself still picking up the pieces after a destructive war. [I]Gone With the Wind[/i] thus had an outsized effect on Japanese culture of the early to mid 1950s, and art from this time (or mimicking this time) in Japan will often contain references to the movie.

title: jolyne_fly_high_with_gucci
body:
A full-color one-shot manga featured in the February 2013 issue of Shueisha's women's fashion magazine, Spur on December 22, 2012. It is the second JoJo-related one-shot published in Spur.
The one-shot was made in collaboration with creative director Frida Giannini of Gucci and was inspired by her 2013 Cruise collection.

It features the protagonist of Stone Ocean, [[kujo jolyne|Jolyne Cujoh]], as well as several characters from Vento Aureo. The story is set in an independent continuity which contradicts the events of the series. 

h4. External links

* https://jojo.fandom.com/wiki/Jolyne,_Fly_High_with_GUCCI

title: bed
body:
A piece of furniture used for [[sleeping]].

Use this tag only if the bed is [b]clearly[/b] there rather than implied. If [[pillow]], bed edges, headboard, frames of any sort are not visible, use [[bed sheet]] without [[bed]].

The traditional, Japanese equivalent is the [[futon]].

title: tooth_pulling
body:
Refers to the process of removing a character's [[tooth]]/[[teeth]], loose or otherwise. Can be done through various means but the most common methods involve the use of [[pliers]], [[string]] wrapped around said tooth, or fingers. 

While it [i]can[/i] be done for children who naturally lose their baby teeth as they age, tooth pulling is most commonly seen in [[ryona]]/[[reverse ryona]] artworks as a means of [[torture|torturing]] the character pictured.

title: reah_(ys)
body:
One of the twin goddesses of the [[Ys]] series. Appears in the [[Ancient Ys Vanished]] duology and their distant prequel [[Ys Origin]].

Her younger twin sister is [[Feena (Ys)|]]. Reah can be distinguished by her longer bangs that occasionally go [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]].

title: feena_(ys)
body:
One of the twin goddesses of the [[Ys]] series. Appears in the [[Ancient Ys Vanished]] duology and their distant prequel [[Ys Origin]].

Her older twin sister is [[Reah (Ys)|]]. Feena can be distinguished by her more noticeable [[curtained hair]] and/or distinctly [[parted bangs]].
